title: For Sale:  A weekend of shooting fun!
postcontent: Read this if you enjoy shooting guns!!  Are you bored with the typical range session?  Standing still and shooting paper no longer interest you?  We have the solution!  A couple buddies and I sat down one day and decided to change the way we shoot.  We all had the tacticool rifles and pistols.  We had a pile of ammo suitable for a Zombie invasion.  We had vests, holsters, and other gear.  But we never put all this stuff to use the way it was intended.  We started up a club and named it RAC FRAG, or Responsible Armed Citizens, Fun Run And Gun.  We made custom steel targets.  We made shooting stations.  We set up a course that involves running from station to station and shooting the steel targets at various ranges.  We transition from long range rifle targets to close up pistol targets, and back again.  You can't help but smile when you hear that BANG on the steel plates.  Every gunner gets videoed and timed on their run so it puts a touch of stress into the mix.  This course teaches you how to set up your gear, make quick mag changes, shoot while on the move, and shoot while shaking and out of breath.    We found a fantastic piece of land near Madison Lake MN that we leased to hold our events. Here is a link to my worst run of the day during our last event to show you we are not super tactical operators and you have nothing to be intimidated by:  http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dG9hslsjdRw        We are all having an absolutely superb time doing this.  If you don't have guns and you want to run with us, we have plenty of guns for you to borrow at no cost as long as you pay for the ammo.  Our next big shoot is Saturday, June 28, and we are also going to camp out and shoot all day Sunday too for anybody that might want to join us.   Cost is $75 per person, or $120 to camp overnight and have another day of shooting fun.  We have a generator on site, a portable toilet, and a grill for whatever you want to bring to cook.  We are looking for more people to add to our club so if this sounds like something you might be interested in, respond to this ad and lets chat!  Please let me know if you have any questions or if you want more info.  Check out our website for more pics and videos:   http://rac-frag.weebly.com/  Feel free to register on our home page for our June 28 shoot to hold your spot.  If you register, you will also be placed on our mailing list for regular FRAG updates.  Thanks!!  Cody

title: For Sale:  FN SPR A5M TBM 25" - Doc'd from FN at SUB 1/4 MOA!
postcontent:
FN Herstal SPR A5M TBM (Special Police Rifle, Tactical Box Magazine) in the 25 inch barrel configuration. Used and very well maintained with a total of 30 documented shots between the factory and me. This gun is A-1 BAD! There are certain weapons when you put them in your hands you know they are heart breakers and life takers and this is one of them. At nearly 12 lbs it's a beast that's not easy to get through the brush but to be frank this beaut wasn't made to take animals of the four legged variety. 
  See the pic that shows the initial factory 3 round zeroing, that's three shots in .23 or sub 1/4 MOA! I have not found one SPR in any config documented from factory better, you want accuracy here it is. It took me a long time to find a rifle in any config with that kind of documented accuracy out of the box. It's a rock solid, no flash, hide in the shadows tac-driver. If you know about these rifles then you know what you're looking at is something you are not going to find often. 
  The weapon's always functioned flawlessly and throws bullets down range like a dream. Scope not included. The accessories that are included are a set of Leupold QD 1" rings, two sets of BlackHawk Twist lock sling swivels for use in any of the rifles 6 QD locations, one set in the standard sling swivel config and one set in the HK snap hook config. Also included is a tactical sling, and a Harris BRS swivel action bipod. An advantage the A5M TBM models have over all the other SPR models is that, while some of the other SPR models do use a magazine setup instead of the longer to load and less efficient hinged floorplate design, the A5M TBM's all come with a 5 round magazine instead of the non-TBM standard 4 round Magazines. Also having the TBM setup on the A5M enables the weapon to use factory FN ten rounds magazines, a full 150% higher firing capacity than the hinged floor plate and standard magazine models (both at 4 rounds). Here along with the standard 5rd TBMag I've included an extra 10rd FN Manufactured TBMag. 
  Bottom line this thing is a beast and you will NEVER find a better out of the box bolt action rifle. Here's a link to the FN USA website page on this exact weapon, http://www.fnhusa.com/l/products/rifles/spr-series/spr-a5m/ . $2,500 cash OBO.
